13 March 2016On Monday, 14 March at 10h00, The Minister of Transport, Dipuo Peters will brief the media on the findings of the PRASA Rail Denver station rear-end collision which left 240 people injured. The Board of inquiry was assigned to investigate the cause of collision involving Metroplus express train 0600 and Business express 1602 at the Denver station in Johannesburg on 28 April 2015 at around 07:10am. The briefing will be held at Tshedimosetso House (GCIS), Pretoria with a link up to Imbizo Media Centre, Cape Town. On Thursday, 17 March at 10h00, The Minister in the Presidency for Planning, Monitoring and Evaluation, Jeff Radebe will address media on the outcomes of the Cabinet meeting to be held on Wednesday, 16 March 2016. Full details will be communicated through a media advisory during the week.In addition to these media briefings, Ministers participate in various public events. For a comprehensive list of national and provincial government activities visit www.gov.za. Should there be changes in the information above, members of the media will be notified accordingly.Enquiries: Nebo Legoabe Cell: 082 453 2874Issued by Government Communication and Information System